The paper deals with geometric problems involving points colored by two colors, which is a topic that falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The motivation behind studying these problems is their frequent occurrence in fields like machine learning and data mining, which suggests that the paper could also belong to sub-categories like data structures (cs.DS), data mining (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes novel techniques for solving these problems, which could also make it relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
